			<ns0:name>k...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/112873510090665368075/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Note that this change will also require changes in other projects (Mono NaCl port, V8 NaCl port).

I'm not at all convinced this change will be a net win in average (we remove some nops but add some arithmetical operations to ALL returns from ALL functions) - and there are no easy way to mix and match the existing style with this new style. Theoretically it's possible to introduce boundary which separates "old style code" from "new style code" and even accommodate both styles in a single binary, but this is brittle and error-prone approach which needs some tangible benefits as justification.

At this point I'm not even sure the whole endeavor is worthwhile.
